#### Install
```bash
$ [sudo] pip install travis-yml
```

#### How it works
based on `.travis.yml` known keys from [Travis Documentation](https://docs.travis-ci.com/)

#### Classes

###### `travis_yml.TravisYML`

method|description
-|-
`load(path)`|load from .travis.yml file
`save(path='.travis.yml')`|save to file

@property|description
-|-
`data`|return dictionary with .travis.yml data

#### Examples
create `.travis.yml` from variables
```python
>>> import travis_yml
>>> travis_yml.TravisYML(language="python", python=["3.4", "3.5"]).save(".travis.yml")
```

create `.travis.yml` with `travis_yml.TravisYML` subclass
```python
>>> class MyTravis(travis_yml.TravisYML):
    language = "python"

    @property
    def python(self):
        versions = ["3.4", "3.5"]
        if "3 :: Only" not in open("classsifiers.txt").read():
            versions += ["2.7"]
        return versions
>>> MyTravis().save(".travis.yml")
```

